<h3> Basti </h3>
<p> After checking out, we drove to a tour of the rainforest just behind Apollo Bay. This was really not very long, but more impressive than the paid tour yesterday in the Otway Fly Treetop. We really took some photos and let ourselves be photographed one time or another. </p>
<h3> Steffi </h3>
<p> When the journey continued, the "sanitary facilities" problem reported shortly afterwards. The next option should be many kilometers away according to the navigation system and so we made a detour of a few km because there should be a campsite. This detour then turned out to be a damn good decision, because after a short time we discovered 2-3 cars on the side of the road and their owners, all of which stared at the air. "What's going on here?" Temp reduced and then we saw it: Lauter koalas were sitting in the trees !!! So stopped on the left, the camera pulled out and go to the Koalas! Juhu, our first free -living koalas on this trip. They don't count on Philipp Island, they were finally under care! </p>
<p> The Koalas in the trees were even quite active and climbed from A to B and presented themselves to the "spectators". So of course everything was forgotten and we stayed there for some time. Over time, however, the actual project was set in again and we continued, but not without continuing to look into the trees, where we could actually keep koalas again and again. At one point we stopped again because the Koalas were quite far down where you could watch them great. </p>
<p> Then the trip finally took us to the long -awaited campsite! Under the pretext of some questions in general, we were able to visit the sanitary facilities before we went back to the original route. You put up with such detours. Or? </p>

