    <p></p> Yes, driving the street to the Otway Lighthouse and thereby seeing the Koalas was a good idea. But there were also really many and above all active animals. <p> After we were back on the Great Ocean Road, we still had a few km through the flat area in front of us before going up to the most beautiful cliffs in the world. We decided to stop directly at the first parking lot and take a look. Kurz became long and once again Steffi's camera ran hot from many photos. </p>
    <p> But it is also really nice to stand in front of these huge rock formations down on the beach, with your feet in the much too cold water and just enjoy the day. There were a few more people on this beach. Nevertheless, there were no more than 10 or 15 people. Of course mostly asian and accordingly quickly away. </p>
    <p> After we had finally torn down from the sight and the steps were up again, the few missing km to the official outlet on the twelve apostles. The parking lot was of course already packed, so that we had to park on a bus parking lot together with another camper. Right next to the parking lot was the runway for the sightseeing flights. </p>
