    <p> Initially, I had actually planned to get into a helicopter here and look at the apostles from above. But after we saw how short the flights were and how extremely overpriced they are, we left it and made our way to the viewing platform on foot. There we also let the camera run hot again and enjoyed the sight of the rock formations in the fog of the breaking waves. </p>
    <p> After a while we went back to the car and treated ourselves to an ice cream for the long way of just 150m as a way. You could starve! After we left the parking lot, we found very quickly that we won't go very far today. Every few hundred meters, a parking space with a viewpoint came along a very nice coastal strip. </p>
