    <p> After the cameras had run hot countless times, we arrived in Port Campbell. There we first drove to the campsite from our camping guide. Unfortunately, this was not according to our taste and we drove on to a larger one that was also in the "city center". If you can call this nest as a city. As so often, this was not the cheapest, but well equipped and directly at a river mouth with its own beach access. </p>
    <p> But we were hungry again and decided to search for something edible. Very quickly we had to find out here that we are just too early. But then we were lucky and landed in a restaurant/pub with a view of the bay and the sunset. There was rump steak for both of us, which was delicious but too much as always. A portion of both of us would have been completely sufficient. </p>
    <p> After eating, we both rolled towards each other towards the beach and enjoyed the increasingly colorful sky in front of the setting sun. When it slowly became too fresh, we went back to the campsite and started with the mandatory program for tonight. To make the laundry! In the meantime we are showered and in bed, a load of clothes still wobbles in the dryer. We just empty it tomorrow morning. Now it is obeyed on the mattress. </p>
